events.description: 64. By the 20th September, we were attack- ing strong enemy positions about Tonzang, the first town of any size after leaving the Imphal Plain. By the 22nd, a double advance from the north and south made the Japanese evacuate this place without opposition, but severe punishment was inflicted on their re- treating columns. Tonzang was full of enemy dead and much equipment was captured.

events.description: 52. No air attacks developed, but the U-boat pack, whose performance so far had been mediocre, made a final effort to redeem their failure. In spite of vigorous counter-attacks by the powerful escort, they succeeded in sink- ing the minesweeper LEDA (Commander A. H.
